{
  "stem": "18581.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 281.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So people started to hoard, to buy more.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Hoarding up.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So those that had goods could sell them at better prices.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was a while-- a while-- that it created even a little boom.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But afterwards, when the-- the Russian officers started to grab everything, and there was no replacement, and there was a shortage, then, of course, prices jacked up.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Did you ever have any direct contact with the Russian soldiers during the Russian occupation of Vilna?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You mean in 1940?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From 19-- from when they come in, in the fall of '39, until June of '41.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There-- there-- there was a, I believe, there was a-- a fellow called [NON-ENGLISH], Lieutenant Colonel, the [NON-ENGLISH]-- that means the military commander of Vilna-- who apparently was a son of Russian nobility.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Officers, and-- who probably did not tell, or somehow decided, probably in-- in 19-- in the early '20s, maybe, to throw in his lot with the Russians.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he and his wife were very gentle and very nice and very well-educated.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the other hand, I met some that were quite anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A-- one-- one Russian officer, when he heard my name, Trigubov-- which-- which means, in Russian-- I don't even know how we got the-- the name Trigubov-- it means the man of the three lips.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Three [RUSSIAN].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when he heard it, he thought that I was a Russian.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was very happy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I told him, [NON-ENGLISH]-- I am a Jew-- he said, how dare you to call yourself such a Russian aristocracy name?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or a Siberian aristocracy name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I said, well, I-- I don't know how I got the name.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we were always called Trigubov.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
